title: Chernoff bound
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

Assume $$X$$ to be a real-valued random variable such that the Laplace transform $$\mathscr{L}_X(\alpha)$$ is finite on $$\ropenI{0,\alpha^*}$$ (could be the wrong interval). Let $$\psi_X(\alpha)$$ be the cumulant generating function of $$X$$$. Then we have
$$
\prob(X \ge \varepsilon) \le e^{-\psi_X^*(\varepsilon)}.
$$